  "text": ". The aim of the pheromone value update rule is to increase the pheromone values on solution components that have been found in high quality solutions. Most ACO algorithms use a variation of the following update rule: [CITATION_1] for , and . Instantiations of this update rule are obtained by different specifications of , which-in all cases that we consider in this paper-is a subset of , where is the set of solutions that were constructed in the current iteration, and is the best-so-far solution. The parameter is called evaporation rate. It has the function of uniformly decreasing all the pheromone values. From a practical point of view, pheromone evaporation is needed to avoid a too rapid convergence of the algorithm toward a suboptimal region. It implements a useful form of forgetting, favoring the exploration of new areas in the search space.",
